article.headline: Cent. Arkansas 107, E. Illinois 96
article.story: CONWAY, Ark. -- Eastern Illinois hit two last-second shots to force overtimes, but Central Arkansas was able to pull away in the second overtime for a 107-96 victory on Saturday. LaQuentin Miles scored 22 points and Terry Tidwell added 18 for Central Arkansas (2-3). The Bears went on a 9-0 run in the second overtime to put it away. Jeremy Granger ended regulation with a 3-pointer for Eastern Illinois (3-2) to tie the score at 77. He finished with 27 points. Joey Miller hit a 3-pointer at the buzzer at the end of the first overtime period to tie the game at 89.
